-- Japanese Sold Net 117.4 Billion Yen Overseas Debt Last Week
-- B y   M i n h   B u i
-- 2013-04-03T23:51:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-03/japanese-sold-net-117-4-billion-yen-overseas-debt-last-week.html
Japanese investors were net
sellers of foreign bonds during the week ended March 29 according
to figures based on reports from designated major investors
released by the Ministry of Finance in  Tokyo .  Japanese investors sold 117.4 billion yen ($1.3 billion)
in overseas bonds and notes, sold 71.8 billion yen in overseas stocks
and sold 129.3 billion yen in overseas short term securities.
That results in a total net sale of 318.5 billion yen.  Foreign investors bought 747.8 billion yen in Japanese bonds,
bought 228.1 billion yen in stocks, and sold 2797.8 billion yen in
short term securities, resulting in a total net sale 1821.9
billion yen.    To contact the reporter on this story:
